sentences: Susan Maughan (born Marian Maughan, 1 July 1938) is an English singer who released successful singles in the 1960s.
Susan Maughan (born Marian Maughan, 1 July 1938) is an English singer who released successful singles in the 1960s.
Her most famous and successful song, "Bobby's Girl" (a cover of the Marcie Blane single), reached number three in the UK Singles Chart at Christmas time in 1962.

"Susan's family moved to Birmingham (in 1953) when Susan was 15.
An immediate audition was arranged, and Susan joined this fine band and sang happily with them for three years.

In September 1961 Susan decided to try her luck in London, and during her brief 36-hour visit she won not only a recording contract but also a year's contract as featured singer with the Ray Ellington Quartet.
